        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare inclusion myopathy characterized by hypotonia and axial muscle weakness leading to spinal rigidity and development of scoliosis and other deformities which can result in respiratory failure. The symptoms are apparent from birth or early childhood. The muscle weakness is not progressive and most patients remain ambulatory. Muscle biopsies show variable myopathic changes."
        },
